result.name: St. Barts

reviews.text: My favourite restaurant in the neighbourhood ！ wonderful environment and atmosphere, families welcome, except the mosquitos please

What else can I complain from good food, nice dessert, friendly service, comfortable seating, free parking and weekly specials? I thought the salmon is already spectacular until I had the ice cream with fried coconut wraping. I have enjoyed my nights and keep it up! :D

Disappointing. Set dinner not available tonight Thursday. No reason given. Bucket of steamed mussels delivered to table cold. Quinoa salad was a plate of greens with a sprinkling of quinoa grains. Haloumi cheese was very hard and very, very salty - inedible. Neither the banoffi nor the creme brulee dessert was authentic. Menu should make this clear. Tuna sashimi salad, beef burger and Prosecco wine were all good. Service was excellent.
Warm atmosphere, great seafood platter.

We had a good evening at St. Barts, 4/5 of the dishes we ordered faired well considering the fairly hefty price tag at the end. The Wagyu cheek wasn't bad it just wasn't exceptional. The staff are friendly if a little slow at times. It's not especially conveniently located but our meal was definitely good enough to warrant a return trip.
